[thinking] **Considering compilation order**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm pondering whether to move the Java helper to src/test/scala, ensuring it gets included during the compile process. The SourceSet.scala seems to account for src/test/scala only, while Java source in src/test/java might be compiled before ScalaCompile. That could mean Scala can't reference it if compileJava occurs first. I wonder if test Java compile needs to happen after the main compilation. Also, does compileTestScala depend on compileTestJava or vice versa? Good questions to sort out!
